_entry.TEXT: Well, you killed all of my body parts by dealing damage to them. You've completed the demo. I'm not sure where we go from here.

parts.TEXT: My sweet parts. Hell, I loved them.

go.TEXT: Well, normally, I'd drop my shield and begin trying to deal some serious damage to yourself with an arrangement of complex bullet situations.

drop.TEXT: I guess I'd still do that...if you'd buy the whole game. But that's impossible.

normally.TEXT: I just don't see a reason! To do this thing! At this time! When I could just...

just.TEXT: ...just keep the shield up...hang out...take it easy. I dunno. I don't have any plans. What do you think?

marry.TEXT: This is highly unorthodox...but yes, I will be your husband. We are married now. Talk to you later, honey.
